Former Fafi MP Maj (Rtd) Aden Sugow on Saturday launched his campaign for the Garissa Senate seat.He said he would perform his oversight role correctly.Addressing his supporters in Garissa town, Sugow said there is a gap in Garissa regarding oversight. He accused Senator Yussuf Haji for failing to deliver on his mandate and not performing his role.&ldquo; I promise to table legislation that will ensure a good chunk of the money the county gets every year is channelled to the subcounties because that is where essential services are lacking,&rdquo; Sugow said in Garissa Ndogo. He urged the electorate to shun politics of ethnicity and instead vote on merit.